# CI/CD Pipeline

## Workflow Structure
```
validate.yml (on: push/PR to main)
  ├── lint
  │     ├── ruff check .
  │     ├── ruff format --check . (or black --check .)
  │     └── mypy app/ (if enabled)
  ├── test
  │     └── pytest -q
  └── security
        └── pip-audit

deploy.yml (on: workflow_dispatch)
  ├── Build Docker image
  ├── Push to registry
  └── Deploy to target environment
```

## Rules for GitHub Actions Changes
- Never skip CI steps without team approval
- Secrets via GitHub repository/environment secrets — never hardcoded
- `concurrency` group prevents duplicate workflow runs (cancel-in-progress: true)

## Merge Rules
- Squash merge to `main` only
- All jobs in `validate.yml` must be green before merge
- Branch protection enforced on `main`

## Deploy
- Manual trigger only via `workflow_dispatch`
- Production deploy requires lint + test + security checks green
- Docker image should be immutable/tagged (commit SHA or release tag)
